asleep is you, Ryo.

198
00:13:49,895 --> 00:13:52,830
A sleeping pill will take care of him
until tomorrow morning.

199
00:13:53,032 --> 00:13:55,534
Kaori, I won't let you disturb
my mokkori business.

200
00:13:55,534 --> 00:13:58,162
I'll put you into a deep sleep
until tomorrow morning.

201
00:14:00,139 --> 00:14:04,542
I don't know why, but it's very
tense in here with those two.

202
00:14:06,612 --> 00:14:09,748
Kaori, aren't you tired?

203
00:14:09,748 --> 00:14:12,774
I'm just giving her a shoulder massage.

204
00:14:13,419 --> 00:14:15,387
It's obvious that he's plotting something.

205
00:14:15,387 --> 00:14:18,083
Oh, not as much as you, brother.

206
00:14:20,125 --> 00:14:22,595
Oh, a female streaking outside
of the window!

207
00:14:22,595 --> 00:14:24,263
What? Where?!

208
00:14:24,263 --> 00:14:26,629
What are you talking about?
This is the fourth floor!

209
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,435
Joking! I was just joking!

210
00:14:29,435 --> 00:14:33,672
Ah! There's a huge cockroach that
looks like a rat over there!

211
00:14:33,672 --> 00:14:37,130
What?! There's no way there could be
a cockroach like that!

212
00:14:37,743 --> 00:14:38,878
Joking! I was just joking!

213
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:42,041
Anyway, cheers!

214
00:14:47,119 --> 00:14:50,452
I can't believe there are people
who can't drink.

215
00:14:58,597 --> 00:15:00,900
They're a strange pair of siblings,

216
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:04,336
but while I'm with them, I somehow
feel at ease.

217
00:15:09,875 --> 00:15:11,240
Goodnight.

218
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:14,546
Ami...

219
00:15:14,546 --> 00:15:17,208
No, no way!

220
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:35,896
That's a sad sound.

221
00:15:36,735 --> 00:15:38,237
Mr. Saeba...

222
00:15:38,237 --> 00:15:41,040
I'm surprised. You're very good.

223
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:42,775
Do you want to be a pianist?

224
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:46,302
This piano... My sister bought it for me.

225
00:15:47,913 --> 00:15:52,017
My parents died four years ago
in a traffic accident,

226
00:15:52,017 --> 00:15:55,387
and it was then that I gave up
becoming a musician.

227
00:15:55,387 --> 00:15:58,557
But my sister started to work,

228
00:15:58,557 --> 00:16:01,293
so I was able to go to college
to study music.

229
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:04,126
I know that she had her own dream.

230
00:16:05,264 --> 00:16:08,467
My sister used to say that her dream

231
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:11,493
was for me to become a famous pianist.

232
00:16:12,171 --> 00:16:15,274
She would say that I'd win
the Chopin Competition

233
00:16:15,274 --> 00:16:18,110
and earn lots of money from concert tours.

234
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:21,647
Then it would be her turn to take it easy.

235
00:16:21,647 --> 00:16:25,048
My sister would always talk about
such dream-like things.

236
00:16:28,854 --> 00:16:32,558
Oh, well, it's a nice day today.

237
00:16:32,558 --> 00:16:34,326
I guess you've been stuck inside
for a long time

238
00:16:34,326 --> 00:16:35,894
since you're thinking like that,
haven't you?

239
00:16:35,894 --> 00:16:39,159
For once, why don't you go out
and have fun?

240
00:16:40,099 --> 00:16:43,398
I'm sorry, but I don't feel like doing that.

241
00:16:44,069 --> 00:16:46,739
Now, now, if you continue like this,

242
00:16:46,739 --> 00:16:49,333
Ami's dream won't come true.

243
00:16:50,376 --> 00:16:53,812
It's certain that your piano playing
technique is incredible,

244
00:16:53,812 --> 00:16:58,146
however, I guess that your music
died when your sister did.

245
00:16:58,717 --> 00:17:02,676
I can't hear anything but sadness from
the sound you play now.

246
00:17:03,122 --> 00:17:07,326
It's impossible to impress people
with a sound like that.

247
00:17:07,326 --> 00:17:10,386
To become a famous pianist
is beyond a dream.

248
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:14,897
You can't be sad and stay inside
of your house forever.

249
00:17:15,434 --> 00:17:18,733
You have to put an end to your sister's
tragedy as soon as possible!

250
00:17:22,007 --> 00:17:23,099
Now...

251
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:26,311
Let's go out and party! Right, right, right?!

252
00:17:26,311 --> 00:17:29,181
But all of a sudden...

253
